  "texts": [
    "For example, recent studies have found that LLMs can predict the directional relationships between ideological attitudes 46, approximate the voting choices of different social groups 47, and mirror human behavior in economic games 48 and reasoning tasks 49, as well as pass theory of mind tests 50.",
    "Our studies focused on predicting the perceived personality of public figures with sufficient presence in the sample used to train GPT-3.",
    "Yet, a similar approach could be used to measure the perceived personality of people absent from the training data.",
    "Given a sample of text describing an individual, one could estimate its location in the model's semantic space and convert it into perceived personality using regression models trained on public figures.",
    "Another limitation of our approach is that it requires collecting human ratings to train regression models."
  ],
